tive leveraging renewal book stability advantage including book size plus retention rate plus book age plus recurring revenue baseline documentation supporting full 24-month averaging without declining-trend haircuts. B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp documentation for agency equity K-1 distributions with 2-year personal returns plus 2-year agency entity returns Form 1065 partnership or Form 1120-S S-corp plus K-1 schedules plus shareholder or partnership agreement excerpt plus ownership percentage plus Form 1084 cash-flow analysis at agency entity level adding back depreciation plus amortization plus customer list amortization plus business use of agency office plus entity non-cash expenses with owner share at ownership percentage. Post-2022 Florida property insurance crisis context including Citizens Property Insurance Corporation surge to 1.4M+ policyholders at peak plus multiple carrier insolvencies United Property & Casualty plus carrier withdrawals plus sustained statewide premium increases. 2022 Senate Bill 2A reform plus 2023 Senate Bill 7052 reform: assignment of benefits AOB litigation reduction plus attorneys fee provisions plus Citizens eligibility tightening plus reinsurance support programs Florida Reinsurance Assistance Program. Excess & Surplus E&S Lines market growth post-2022 crisis with Florida Surplus Lines Service Office FSLSO compliance plus non-admitted carrier appointments plus HNW coastal property plus complex commercial risks. Hurricane Ian September 2022 $109B+ damages substantially impacted Florida reinsurance environment. Citizens Property Insurance depopulation programs returning policies to private carriers as market stabilizes. Florida HNW + UHNW wealth migration sustaining high-value homeowners insurance demand $5M-$25M+ property tiers. Post-Surfside SB 4-D condo insurance impact. Insurtech competition adaptation through agency management systems Vertafore Applied Systems EZLynx. Agency M&A activity 2024-2026 with consolidator plus PE-backed buyer activity at 2-4x annual revenue valuations. Conventional Jumbo for HNW multi-licensed agency owners. Bank Statement Non-QM for high-add-back solo agency owners. P&L Statement Non-QM for established multi-producer agencies with true expense ratio 30-45%. Asset-Depletion Non-QM for post-agency-sale or transition. DSCR Non-QM for investment property scaling. Construction-to-Permanent for agency principals building custom home. Cash-Out Refinance for agency book acquisition + M&A + producer buy-in. Multi-state insurance license mobility through non-resident licensure. Multi-source synthesis combining commission plus profit sharing plus overrides plus K-1 plus spouse W-2." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-advisors/insurance-agency-owner/">
